	abstract = {Compared to traditional vehicles, electric vehicles (EVs) with in-wheel motors (IWMs) have several distinguishing features in terms of control including: (1) fast motor-torque response and high-performance antislip control; (2) measurable motor torque that can be employed for applications such as road condition estimation; and (3) a wheel with an IWM that can freely generate clockwise and counter-clockwise rotation. With these advantages, high performance control of EVs for higher safety, lower energy consumption, and better comfort become possible. However, vehicle parameters and states, either measured or estimated, are essential for all kinds of control applications. This chapter covers modeling, sensing, and estimation techniques and control methods for dynamics control of EVs.},
